der runden die Darstellung ab.  aIn order to obtain standard sections for reproducible interpretation of the results of locomotor ultrasound, standardized section planes are essential. This book offers practical instruction in imaging standard sections as recommended by the German Society for Ultrasound in Medicine (DEGUM). For each standard section, it presents the correct transducer positioning, ultrasound images, and MRI images for comparison.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aDiagnostic ultrasonic imaging.1 aBerthold, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldmann, Axel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHartung, Wolfgang, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM0 cEPUBz97831105350370 cprintz978311053456640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053596940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110535969423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110535969.jpg  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPMb2019